  "title": "Airfreight Customer Service & Operations – Senior Executive",
  "description": "<p><ol><li><p>Manage end-to-end airfreight shipments including booking, documentation, coordination with airlines and ground handlers, customs clearance (imports), export documentation, billing, and shipment closure</p></li><li><p>Serve as the main point of contact for customers, providing timely updates and resolving operational issues</p></li><li><p>Coordinate closely with airlines, trucking partners, customs authorities, and internal teams</p></li><li><p>Monitor shipment progress to ensure compliance with SLAs and internal procedures</p></li><li><p>Proactively manage delays, documentation discrepancies, and shipment exceptions</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate records and shipment documentation</p></li><li><p>Support and guide junior team members where required</p></li></ol></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><ul><li><p>Experience in airfreight forwarding (import and/or export)</p></li><li><p>Strong operational knowledge of airfreight documentation and customs processes</p></li><li><p>Customer-focused mindset with good communication and coordination skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage multiple shipments in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with CargoWise system is preferred</p></li></ul><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p>Reg. No.: R23117344 (Tiong Tian Ho)</p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
